1
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:38,767
<i>The boss wants me to tell you
that you're fired.</i>

2
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,700
<i>I'm doing it for you and Tetay,</i>

3
00:00:40,833 --> 00:00:43,300
<i>because I want my daughter
to be proud of me.</i>

4
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:44,333
<i> Darling?</i>

5
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:45,400
<i>Be strong. You will get
through this.</i>

6
00:00:45,533 --> 00:00:46,567
<i> Be strong, right?</i>

7
00:00:47,533 --> 00:00:50,267
<i> I will never ask mom for help.</i>

8
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:51,400
<i> Jeff?</i>

9
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:53,100
<i>What? Why did you tell her?
To embarrass me?</i>

10
00:00:53,233 --> 00:00:55,000
<i>- She needs to know.
- She needs to know what?</i>

11
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:56,400
<i> That her son is a failure?</i>

12
00:00:56,533 --> 00:00:58,367
<i> Jeff, you are my strength.</i>

13
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:03,633
<i>I am this strong because of you.
Because you protect me.</i>

14
00:01:03,767 --> 00:01:05,033
<i> Mom, I'm sorry.</i>

15
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:08,800
<i>Son, you're not a failure.
You're not a failure.</i>

16
00:01:08,967 --> 00:01:11,800
<i>We're fully cooperating
with CPHSO.</i>

17
00:01:11,933 --> 00:01:14,267
<i>Within our company,
we're already taking action.</i>

18
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:18,100
<i>We also coordinated with all the
people who got food poisoning.</i>

19
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:23,267
<i>I can now rest in peace
while FMP rests in pieces.</i>

20
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:26,867
<i>We have a feeling
that we'd been sabotaged.</i>

21
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:32,100
<i>I had our staff take a video of
the incident for documentation.</i>

22
00:01:32,233 --> 00:01:34,200
<i> Sis, I know this guy.</i>

23
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:35,767
<i>Did you see the way
that man looked?</i>

24
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,733
<i> And Miss Martinez, too.</i>

25
00:01:37,867 --> 00:01:41,000
<i>Is she in cahoots
with Hazel, too?</i>

26
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:46,600
I knew Hazel
was behind all of this.

27
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:49,300
That sneaky little witch
played us.

28
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:52,967
You know, the first time
I saw Alice,

29
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:55,667
I had a strange feeling
about her.

30
00:01:57,667 --> 00:01:59,067
<i> Miss Martinez?</i>

31
00:02:02,033 --> 00:02:04,500
<i> Miss Antonio.</i>

32
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:05,533
<i> Nice meeting you.</i>

33
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:06,500
<i> You look familiar.</i>

34
00:02:06,633 --> 00:02:09,267
<i>I'm sorry,
have I met you before?</i>

35
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,500
<i> I can't point it out.</i>

36
00:02:11,633 --> 00:02:13,967
<i>Many people say I look like
someone they know.</i>

37
00:02:15,167 --> 00:02:16,500
<i> Usually a celebrity.</i>

38
00:02:16,633 --> 00:02:17,933
<i> That's right!</i>

39
00:02:18,067 --> 00:02:20,667
<i> You do look like one!</i>

40
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,933
You know what, Sis?

41
00:02:22,067 --> 00:02:24,300
I've seen that face before.

42
00:02:24,433 --> 00:02:27,433
I've seen her before.
I just can't remember where.

43
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,667
<i> That's Manuel, right?</i>

44
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,400
<i> Who is this girl?</i>

45
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:39,967
For heaven's sake, Paz!

46
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:43,333
How can you forget!

47
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:44,967
- Wait a minute.
- What's going on?

48
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,133
Wait, Sis. I have something
to show you.

49
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,267
If my gut feeling is right,
wait.

50
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:52,433
- Wait, what?
- Hold on, okay? 2007, Saudi.

51
00:02:52,567 --> 00:02:55,000
Confirmed, Sis, look!

52
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:58,000
Look, both of them are here
in Saudi Arabia.

53
00:02:58,133 --> 00:03:01,200
Alice is Hazel's lapdog.

54
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:04,867
Sis, you should sue
these two little goblins!

55
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,367
Sue them, I'm telling you!

56
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:18,100
I'm not just going to sue them.

57
00:03:18,233 --> 00:03:20,900
They'd better be ready
for what I'm about to do.

58
00:03:37,533 --> 00:03:38,833
Oh, you're awake.

59
00:03:40,167 --> 00:03:41,700
What are you doing?

60
00:03:44,033 --> 00:03:46,933
Stage two of my plans.

61
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:52,600
Spy cameras?

62
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:53,933
What for?

63
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,867
For Felma's house.

64
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,133
I want my eyes and ears
inside their walls.

65
00:04:02,567 --> 00:04:04,367
How are you going to get
inside their house?

66
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,533
Aren't you banned
from their village?

67
00:04:06,667 --> 00:04:09,767
Remember, I'm pretending
to be nice.

68
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:12,367
To be fair to that woman,

69
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:15,400
when it comes to being a mother,
she has a soft heart.

70
00:04:16,367 --> 00:04:18,733
That's exactly
what I'll use against her,

71
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:20,733
I'll play the mother card.

72
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,333
You know, I'll say I want
to see Jessica,

73
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:28,433
I'll beg her
so I can get inside.

74
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:34,067
And of course, once I'm in,
I'll put CCTV in her house.

75
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:37,400
Wow, your plan
is something else.

76
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,700
Of course.

77
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:41,100
You know what?

78
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:42,800
I'll always be not just one,

79
00:04:42,933 --> 00:04:45,500
but two or three steps
ahead of them.

80
00:04:48,133 --> 00:04:51,833
Anyway, have you talked
to Jessica lately?

81
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,033
Well...

82
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,867
not yet.

83
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,433
Because I'm giving her space
like she wanted.

84
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,833
But I know my daughter.

85
00:05:02,933 --> 00:05:05,500
Jessica is a good girl.

86
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:07,367
I know that she never
holds a grudge.

87
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:11,267
And once I see her,
when I visit her,

88
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,867
I will make sure...

89
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,100
we'll be on good terms.

90
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,433
Can you confirm if this is her?

91
00:05:24,567 --> 00:05:26,933
Yes, she's Hazel's best friend.

92
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:28,967
She's my godmother.

93
00:05:30,067 --> 00:05:32,900
So Hazel conspired with Alice?

94
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,133
Your mom is something else,
isn't she?

95
00:05:36,267 --> 00:05:38,000
She's dragging innocent people
into this

96
00:05:38,133 --> 00:05:39,733
just to make mom look bad.

97
00:05:42,533 --> 00:05:45,400
By the way, Mom,
how are the victims?

98
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:48,033
They're fine,

99
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:50,600
they're all better now.

100
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:54,400
And they're not going
to sue anymore.

101
00:05:54,533 --> 00:05:56,133
Of course, they won't.

102
00:05:56,267 --> 00:05:58,733
You already made
a settlement with them.

103
00:05:58,867 --> 00:06:02,600
FMP lost income because
of the temporary closure.

104
00:06:02,733 --> 00:06:06,100
And you paid a lot of money
to compensate the victims.

105
00:06:08,967 --> 00:06:10,733
I need to take this call.

106
00:06:10,867 --> 00:06:12,667
- Excuse me.
- Okay.

107
00:06:18,267 --> 00:06:19,667
Hello?

108
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:22,600
Hello, Felma?

109
00:06:22,733 --> 00:06:24,900
Sorry to bother you.

110
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:26,233
<i> It's just...</i>

111
00:06:26,367 --> 00:06:30,567
<i>I'm thinking of going away
for a while to clear my head.</i>

112
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:35,467
But before I do that,
I have one request.

113
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:40,633
Do you think I could visit
Jessica and say goodbye to her

114
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,633
before I leave?

115
00:06:42,767 --> 00:06:44,133
All right.

116
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:48,867
I'll inform the guardhouse
so they'll let you in.

117
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,900
Oh, thank you so much, Felma.

118
00:06:52,033 --> 00:06:53,767
Thank you.

119
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,367
You're welcome.

120
00:07:53,767 --> 00:07:55,167
<i>Your mom is something else,
isn't she?</i>

121
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,900
<i>She's dragging innocent people
into this</i>

122
00:07:57,033 --> 00:07:58,933
<i> just to make mom look bad.</i>

123
00:08:10,967 --> 00:08:13,500
<i>Did you have something
to do with what happened</i>

124
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:15,600
<i> in Luntian Park, Mommy?</i>

125
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,867
Hazel is getting
on my nerves, bestie.

126
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:22,967
She's out of line.

127
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:25,933
I want to pull her hair out!
I want to pull it all out!

128
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:32,833
Bestie, it's too much!

129
00:08:32,967 --> 00:08:35,700
She doesn't care even
if a lot of people get hurt,

130
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:38,100
as long as she can make
my mom look bad.

131
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:39,767
You know, Jeffrey's right.

132
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:41,767
She really is Satan's sibling.

133
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:45,700
Coleen.

134
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:47,333
What?

135
00:08:47,467 --> 00:08:48,933
I'm calling mom.

136
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:50,733
What for?

137
00:08:50,867 --> 00:08:53,033
To tell her
that we know what she did?

138
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:56,400
Wait, we're not sure if she has
something to do with it.

139
00:08:56,567 --> 00:08:58,033
I'm going to call mom
to ask if...

140
00:08:58,167 --> 00:08:59,867
To ask what?

141
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:03,100
Jessica, aren't you
convinced yet?

142
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:05,867
You saw how she conspired
with your godmother!

143
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:09,767
- But, Coleen...
- Jessica, that's enough.

144
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:11,567
You're not going
to tell your mom

145
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:14,567
that my mom knows what she did.

146
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,767
If you do that, Jessica,

147
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:19,167
I will be angrier with you.

148
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,167
Why are you mad at me?

149
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,633
What did I do?

150
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:28,067
<i>We were supposed to go home
tomorrow,</i>

151
00:09:28,233 --> 00:09:32,533
<i>but I begged dad and Aunt Felma
to come home now.</i>

152
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:35,033
<i> Nobody informed me.</i>

153
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:37,833
<i> She seems to have forgiven me.</i>

154
00:09:37,967 --> 00:09:39,300
<i> Really, Mom?</i>

155
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:41,233
<i> That's great news, Auntie.</i>

156
00:09:44,233 --> 00:09:46,133
<i> But they still hate me.</i>

157
00:09:46,267 --> 00:09:48,733
<i> Manuel, be patient.</i>

158
00:09:48,867 --> 00:09:50,700
<i> They will forgive you, too.</i>

159
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:51,567
<i> That's right, Dad.</i>

160
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:53,500
<i> Just be patient.</i>

161
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,333
Coleen...

162
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:04,700
what's the matter?

163
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:07,033
You want to know
what my problem is?

164
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:09,767
It's you, Jessica!

165
00:10:10,767 --> 00:10:12,667
You're my problem.

166
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:17,600
I'm sorry about that, Bestie.

167
00:10:17,733 --> 00:10:19,167
Someone's being annoying.

168
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:39,167
There's no news
from CPHSO yet, Sir.

169
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:42,467
The investigation
is still ongoing.

170
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:46,733
We still don't know
when FMP will resume operations.

171
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:47,700
Yes.

172
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:49,233
Yes, Ma'am.

173
00:10:49,367 --> 00:10:50,867
- Okay.
- What happened at Luntian Park

174
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,367
was just an isolated case,
Ma'am.

175
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,567
- Good morning, Ma'am.
- Yes, good morning.

176
00:10:57,700 --> 00:11:00,267
- Yes, Mr. Roldan.
- Good morning, Ma'am.

177
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:03,467
Yes, thank you.

178
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,133
Thank you very much.

179
00:11:05,267 --> 00:11:07,567
Sis, is that the guy
from City Sanitation?

180
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,133
What did he say?

181
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:15,167
They're waiting for results.

182
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:18,400
For the product samples
that we got tested.

183
00:11:18,533 --> 00:11:22,900
They won't find anything
in those products.

184
00:11:23,033 --> 00:11:26,667
But the products Alice served
at the feeding program

185
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,233
had something.

186
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:30,167
Do the City Sanitation
people know

187
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:33,200
that they found laxatives
on those products?

188
00:11:34,567 --> 00:11:35,733
Yes.

189
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:42,233
I already sent them

190
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:45,467
the notarized documents
from the hospital.

191
00:11:47,267 --> 00:11:48,433
You know what?

192
00:11:48,567 --> 00:11:53,200
Seeing our office not operating
like this makes me so furious!

193
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,900
Can you imagine how I feel?

194
00:11:58,433 --> 00:12:00,733
I'm fed up with Hazel.

195
00:12:05,067 --> 00:12:06,867
Call that Alice Martinez.

196
00:12:08,067 --> 00:12:09,167
Tell her to come here.

197
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,333
Really, Sis?

198
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:16,167
Are we going through our plan
against those two goblins?

199
00:12:26,267 --> 00:12:27,867
Yes, Alice.

200
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,533
According to
the store technician

201
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:36,200
this will last
around 7 to 10 days.

202
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:40,433
I also availed the other package
from the SilentWatch app.

203
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,400
Yes.

204
00:12:42,533 --> 00:12:47,033
I also have...

205
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:52,800
a Direct Sky storage app.
Motion Detection.

206
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:55,700
To make the battery last.

207
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,533
<i> Don't you need Wi-Fi for that?</i>

208
00:12:58,667 --> 00:13:00,367
<i>How are you going to connect
those?</i>

209
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:05,067
Don't worry, I got this.
I have an idea.

210
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,667
<i> All right, good luck!</i>

211
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,267
<i> Don't get caught.</i>

212
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,067
You, too.

213
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:14,233
Listen to me,
just play it cool, okay?

214
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:16,900
Good.

215
00:13:22,567 --> 00:13:24,600
Here I come, Felma.

216
00:13:24,733 --> 00:13:26,967
I'm ready to bring you down.

217
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,900
Hi, Coleen.

218
00:13:43,033 --> 00:13:46,133
Your mom knows that I'm coming.

219
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:50,433
- Felma knows.
-Yes, she told me you're coming.

220
00:13:50,567 --> 00:13:53,900
But dad is at the hospital
for his therapy.

221
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:56,333
And Jessica's at her
follow-up check-up.

222
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:59,367
Oh my, I came here too early.

223
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:03,533
Can I wait inside?
It's raining out here.

224
00:14:03,667 --> 00:14:06,267
Oh, sure. Come in.

225
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,100
- Thank you.
- Okay.

226
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:14,300
Let me help you carry that.

227
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:15,900
This is for you, guys.

228
00:14:16,033 --> 00:14:16,900
Thank you.

229
00:14:18,467 --> 00:14:20,200
Oh my, wait.

230
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:22,200
Wait...

231
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:24,100
It's just...

232
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:28,533
I forgot that I don't have
a signal here.

233
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:30,600
I'm waiting for a video call.

234
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,500
Can I connect to your Wi-Fi?

235
00:14:32,633 --> 00:14:33,500
Is it okay?

236
00:14:33,633 --> 00:14:36,733
- Yeah. Connect to JAC Connect.
- Oh, okay.

237
00:14:36,867 --> 00:14:38,367
Wait.

238
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,700
There it is, JAC.

239
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:40,667
Okay.

240
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,300
You're taking
what isn't yours again.

241
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:45,000
Excuse me?

242
00:14:46,633 --> 00:14:48,933
You're taking
what isn't yours again.

243
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:52,100
All caps, no space.

244
00:14:52,233 --> 00:14:54,033
That's our password.

245
00:14:55,967 --> 00:14:59,333
Yes. We don't condone thieves.

246
00:15:00,467 --> 00:15:01,800
Wi-Fi thieves.

247
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:06,333
- That's the Wi-Fi password.
- Yes.

248
00:15:06,467 --> 00:15:07,567
Oh, yeah.

249
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:09,133
That's quite long.

250
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:11,033
There you go.

251
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:13,767
- That's a cute password.
- You can go inside now.

252
00:15:16,933 --> 00:15:18,933
Thank you. I'm going to leave
my umbrella here, okay?

253
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:20,300
Okay.

254
00:15:24,867 --> 00:15:26,233
Have a seat.

255
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:28,467
Thank you.

256
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:29,767
Thanks for the gift.

257
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,500
I'm going to get you
some snacks.

258
00:15:31,633 --> 00:15:33,567
Oh my, thank you.

259
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,100
What is it?

260
00:15:38,233 --> 00:15:40,400
Hold on, come.

261
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:42,067
What is that witch doing here?

262
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,200
Why did you let her in?

263
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:45,133
Relax, Didang.

264
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:46,633
She's here to visit Jessica.

265
00:15:47,933 --> 00:15:48,700
What do you mean she's here
to visit Jessica?

266
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:50,667
What if she makes a scene again?

267
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:53,033
Does Ma'am Felma know
about this?

268
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:55,333
Yes, of course.

269
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:58,133
But you know
what mom doesn't know?

270
00:15:58,267 --> 00:15:59,167
What?

271
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:07,733
This.

272
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:08,833
This.

273
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:13,667
Didang, calm down.

274
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,367
This is a laxative, isn't it?

275
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,400
This will make...

276
00:16:18,533 --> 00:16:20,367
I know.

277
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:24,567
This is the same laxative
they put in our sisig, right?

278
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:25,967
Yes.

279
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:29,467
I'm just giving her a dose
of her own medicine.

280
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,200
I'm taking revenge.

281
00:16:32,567 --> 00:16:34,267
You know what, this is very bad.

282
00:16:49,933 --> 00:16:50,967
I've got your back.

283
00:16:52,033 --> 00:16:53,833
Pour the whole packet in.

284
00:16:53,967 --> 00:16:57,300
It will make her tummy upset
all day.

285
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:59,300
I will.

286
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:04,833
Can you call mom?
Tell her the visitor is here.

287
00:17:04,967 --> 00:17:06,233
<i> This is perfect.</i>

288
00:17:06,367 --> 00:17:07,167
<i> Fortune plants.</i>

289
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:09,467
<i>They don't need to water
it often.</i>

290
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,800
What visitor?

291
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:17,633
You mean a pest.

292
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:19,067
Didang, that's funny.

293
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,000
You're silly.

294
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:20,967
Pour the whole packet in.

295
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,800
I will.

296
00:17:22,933 --> 00:17:25,300
Okay. I'm going to call
your mom.

297
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:52,867
Yes, Didang.

298
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,367
I'm on my way home.

299
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:56,133
Yes.

300
00:17:56,267 --> 00:17:59,500
Sis, the demon is in our house.

301
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:01,400
Really? Okay, you should go.

302
00:18:01,533 --> 00:18:03,733
I'll take care of Alice.

303
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:04,833
She's on her way here.

304
00:18:04,967 --> 00:18:06,800
- I'll be right back, okay?
- Okay. Take care.

305
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:13,500
Come on, Alice.

306
00:18:13,633 --> 00:18:15,033
Come on now.

307
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:27,033
Miss Hazel, what are you doing
over there?

308
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,867
I dropped my earring here.

309
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,033
Over here.

310
00:18:36,767 --> 00:18:38,100
I found it.

311
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:40,033
Have some snacks.

312
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:45,933
Wow, that looks good!

313
00:18:46,067 --> 00:18:49,500
Of course,
that's my pasta a la Coleen.

314
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:51,133
Really?

315
00:18:51,267 --> 00:18:52,733
Let's have a taste then.

316
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:08,267
It's spicy.

317
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,367
Oh my gosh, I'm sorry,
let me get you another plate.

318
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:13,200
I think I put too many
chili flakes.

319
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:14,667
It's okay.

320
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:20,033
This iced tea is good.

321
00:19:20,167 --> 00:19:22,300
The tea has a strong,
distinct taste.

322
00:19:22,433 --> 00:19:24,033
Where did you buy it?

323
00:19:24,167 --> 00:19:28,167
Oh, that's my own blend,
specially made for you.

324
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:29,600
You're amazing.

325
00:19:29,767 --> 00:19:31,333
You're such a sweet kid.

326
00:19:31,467 --> 00:19:32,867
This is good.

327
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,633
Hi, where's Miss Paz?

328
00:19:49,567 --> 00:19:50,833
Thank you.

329
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:56,867
Hi.

330
00:19:57,867 --> 00:20:00,767
Thank you for coming, Alice.

331
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:02,667
Of course, Sis.

332
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:05,033
What's the emergency meeting?

333
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:07,767
Is FMP back in business?

334
00:20:22,433 --> 00:20:23,800
<i> This is so annoying,</i>

335
00:20:23,933 --> 00:20:26,033
<i>I didn't get to plant
the other camera.</i>

336
00:20:26,167 --> 00:20:29,333
<i>But at least I get to plant
one camera.</i>

337
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:31,067
<i> It's better than nothing.</i>

338
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:37,933
Mom.

339
00:20:40,033 --> 00:20:40,933
Felma.

340
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:43,133
Felma.

341
00:20:48,433 --> 00:20:51,933
Thank you very much

342
00:20:52,067 --> 00:20:54,367
for letting me come here.

343
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,200
To visit Jessica.

344
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,100
Thank you so much.

345
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:14,033
Friend, what's wrong?

346
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:16,433
It's you, Alice.

347
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:19,433
You're my biggest problem!

348
00:21:19,567 --> 00:21:23,433
It's you,
you little goblin traitor!

349
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:26,300
You witch!

350
00:21:35,733 --> 00:21:38,133
Stop pretending, Hazel!

351
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:47,233
What's your problem?

352
00:21:47,367 --> 00:21:48,633
What?

353
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,933
What's going on, Felma?

354
00:21:52,067 --> 00:21:53,267
I thought
we'd patched things up?

355
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:55,167
What is this about?

356
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:56,400
That's what I thought too.

357
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:59,500
I thought...

358
00:21:59,633 --> 00:22:02,767
a demon like you
could still change!

359
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:04,133
Turns out you can't.

360
00:22:05,567 --> 00:22:08,867
You sabotaged my company!

361
00:22:13,033 --> 00:22:14,900
What? What are you talking
about?

362
00:22:15,067 --> 00:22:16,800
What are you saying, Felma?

363
00:22:17,867 --> 00:22:19,500
Don't try to deny it.

364
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:25,100
I have proof.

365
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:31,300
There.

366
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:37,467
Alice Martinez is your friend,
isn't she?

367
00:22:38,533 --> 00:22:43,900
And that man, he was with you
when you barged in here!

368
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:49,833
What?

369
00:22:49,967 --> 00:22:51,233
What?

370
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:54,667
Are you still denying it?

371
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:56,800
You witch!

372
00:22:56,933 --> 00:22:59,700
Look at this.
Watch it carefully.

373
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:01,700
I have proof!

374
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:17,633
What now? Are you still going
to deny it?

375
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:23,733
Tell me how you conspired
with Hazel that monkey!

376
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:24,767
Tell me!

377
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:25,900
Friend, no!

378
00:23:26,033 --> 00:23:27,700
What? Friend?

379
00:23:29,967 --> 00:23:31,533
Ma'am, stop it!

380
00:23:31,667 --> 00:23:34,967
Don't intervene! Go over there!

381
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:39,100
Rose, come here!

382
00:23:39,233 --> 00:23:41,400
Take a video of this ugly witch!

383
00:23:41,533 --> 00:23:43,100
Are you ready?

384
00:23:43,233 --> 00:23:45,233
Come on! You little goblin!

385
00:23:45,367 --> 00:23:50,033
Go on, tell the camera what you,
Hazel, and that monkey did!

386
00:23:50,167 --> 00:23:54,267
Tell them what you did
to the people at Luntian Park!

387
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,267
We didn't do anything wrong,
Paz!

388
00:23:56,433 --> 00:23:57,800
Nothing? You did something!

389
00:23:57,933 --> 00:23:59,667
You did something! You did!

390
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:00,633
Really? You didn't do
anything wrong?

391
00:24:00,767 --> 00:24:02,233
I don't have anything
to confess,

392
00:24:02,367 --> 00:24:03,967
even if you beat me up all day!

393
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:05,300
Oh, so you want
to get beaten up?

394
00:24:05,433 --> 00:24:06,467
Fine then!

395
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,267
Here you go!

396
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:16,100
This is for Felma!

397
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:22,667
Stop!

398
00:24:23,633 --> 00:24:24,800
Stop it!

399
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,567
I don't have anything
to confess.

400
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,167
I have nothing to confess,
because...

401
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:34,433
because I have nothing
to do with that.

402
00:24:36,133 --> 00:24:37,600
Felma,

403
00:24:37,733 --> 00:24:40,200
I'm trying to change
for Jessica.

404
00:24:41,267 --> 00:24:43,800
I don't want to ruin
my relationship with her.

405
00:24:44,767 --> 00:24:46,600
Perhaps you're doing this

406
00:24:46,733 --> 00:24:49,033
to ruin my relationship
with Jessica?

407
00:24:49,167 --> 00:24:50,600
It's right in front of you.

408
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:55,500
- The evidence is right here!
- What evidence?

409
00:24:55,633 --> 00:24:57,333
I wasn't there!

410
00:24:57,467 --> 00:24:59,000
Am I in the video?
Did you see me there?

411
00:24:59,133 --> 00:25:05,433
Okay, I admit that I know Alice
and Maximo, but...

412
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:07,700
It doesn't mean
that I made them do something.

413
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:09,767
That's not true.

414
00:25:09,900 --> 00:25:11,800
Felma,

415
00:25:11,933 --> 00:25:13,833
we're nurses.

416
00:25:13,967 --> 00:25:16,167
Alice is a nurse. She can't do
what you're accusing her of.

417
00:25:16,300 --> 00:25:17,767
We save lives.

418
00:25:17,900 --> 00:25:19,600
We don't hurt people.

419
00:25:19,733 --> 00:25:21,800
Right? Don't accuse us
of any wrongdoing.

420
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:23,933
Don't accuse us, Felma.

421
00:25:27,667 --> 00:25:29,500
Stop faking it.

422
00:25:31,367 --> 00:25:36,133
You dragged so many people
into this!

423
00:25:36,300 --> 00:25:37,333
My family!

424
00:25:38,767 --> 00:25:41,933
The people at Luntian Park!

425
00:25:42,067 --> 00:25:46,400
Even my FMP staff!

426
00:25:46,533 --> 00:25:48,167
I still have something
to do at the office.

427
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:50,900
Paz and I still have something
to take care of.

428
00:25:52,567 --> 00:25:54,433
You monsters!

429
00:25:56,100 --> 00:25:58,467
Sweetie, I'm in the hospital.

430
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:02,233
I suffered from severe
diarrhea and cramping.

431
00:26:02,367 --> 00:26:03,533
Mom, are you okay?

432
00:26:03,667 --> 00:26:07,133
I had a massive intake
of laxatives.

433
00:26:07,267 --> 00:26:11,733
So it's true, you
and Auntie Alice had laxatives.

434
00:26:11,900 --> 00:26:15,033
You put it on the sisig
they served at the park.

435
00:26:15,167 --> 00:26:17,333
Coleen did this to me.

436
00:26:17,467 --> 00:26:20,133
She put a laxative in my drink.

437
00:26:20,267 --> 00:26:21,967
Who are you talking to?

438
00:26:22,100 --> 00:26:24,067
Your liar mom?

439
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:27,033
What are you two talking about?

440
00:26:27,167 --> 00:26:28,433
Is it true?

441
00:26:28,567 --> 00:26:32,333
Did you put laxatives
in my mom's drink?
